      C(y, y)\ar [r, "\eta _y^{-1}"]\ar [d, "t_*"'] & C(x, y)\ar [d, "t_*"] \\
      C(y, x)\ar [r, "\eta _x^{-1}"'] & C(x, x)
    \end {tikzcd}



  commutes. Following 1_y around the top and right, we get       t_*(\eta _y^{-1}(1_y)) = t_*(u) = tu,    while on the left and bottom we get      \eta _x^{-1}(t_*(1_y)) = \eta _x^{-1}(t) = 1_x,   
  so again tu = 1_x. This completes the proof.

